## Phase 1 – Advanced DSA + ML Depth (Months 1–12 Second Year)

### 1. DSA – Strong Medium + Hard
Focus: Medium mastery + hard patterns  

Monthly Plan  
Months 1–3  
- Advanced arrays/strings: Kadane variants, sliding window hard, two pointers deep  
- Binary search hard: rotated variants, kth smallest advanced  
- Linked list/Stack/Queue hard: LRU full, next greater both sides  

Months 4–6  
- Recursion/Backtracking: subsets II, N-Queens, word break II  
- Trees/BST: diameter, LCA, kth smallest BST  
- Graphs medium: BFS/DFS grid, shortest path intro  

Months 7–9  
- Heaps hard: median stream, task scheduler  
- Greedy/DP 1D: knapsack variants, LIS, house robber  
- Company medium-hard (Amazon, Microsoft, Google tagged)  

Months 10–12  
- Mock contests (LeetCode weekly, Codeforces virtual)  
- Revision cycles (7/30/90 days)  

Target: 900–1400 total (600–900 medium, 200–400 hard)  

Resources  
- Striver SDE Sheet + A2Z  
- Love Babbar company lists  
- takeUforward hard series  
- LeetCode company tags  

